  "narrative": {
    "intro": "Total federal contract obligations in Maine for FY2026 to date are $1.2B. Obligations fell 70.0% year over year. There were 6,284 awards with an average award size of $187K. Obligations by fiscal year show a peak of $3.9B in FY25, following $3.7B in FY24 and FY23, $2.7B in FY22, and $2.4B in FY21; FY26 is $1.2B to date. The Department of Defense accounts for the largest share of FY2026 to date obligations at $1.1B, followed by the Department of Veterans Affairs at $22.9M and the Department of Agriculture at $18.4M. The largest vendors in Maine for FY2026 to date are BATH IRON WORKS CORPORATION at $445M and MARTINS POINT HEALTH CARE INC at $433M, with additional major vendors including 381 CONSTRUCTORS at $63.9M and MOHAWK NORTHEAST INC at $24.4M. By industry, Ship Building and Repairing totals $455M and Direct Health and Medical Insurance Carriers total $433M. All figures are contract obligations; current-year totals are partial (fiscal year to date).",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "What changed in FY2026 to date compared with prior fiscal years?",
        "body": "Obligations fell 70.0% year over year to $1.2B for FY2026 to date. This follows $3.9B in FY25, $3.7B in FY24 and FY23, $2.7B in FY22, and $2.4B in FY21. The count of awards in FY2026 to date is 6,284 with an average award size of $187K. Current-year totals are partial (fiscal year to date)."
      },
      {
        "heading": "Which agencies, vendors, and industries dominate federal contracting in Maine right now?",
        "body": "The Department of Defense dominates FY2026 to date obligations at $1.1B, with the Department of Veterans Affairs at $22.9M and the Department of Agriculture at $18.4M. Top vendors include BATH IRON WORKS CORPORATION at $445M and MARTINS POINT HEALTH CARE INC at $433M, followed by 381 CONSTRUCTORS at $63.9M. Leading industries are Ship Building and Repairing at $455M and Direct Health and Medical Insurance Carriers at $433M."
      }
    ]
